                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Early nineteenth-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <desc>Fine and careful.</desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; names of the ruler, of the commissioner and other individuals; a few lines (alternating with black lines) and one
                           group of lines in the opening page of each section of the text; two initial lines of the first commemorative note of the day and one
                           initial line of the subsequent commemorative note of the day; the word <foreign xml:lang="gez">salām</foreign> opening the salām-hymns; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           Ethiopic numerals or their elements.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="35vb" to="36rc"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Tarik za-taṣǝḥfa ba-mawāʿǝlihomu la-naguśa nagaśt Yoḥannǝs, 
                              ‘History that was written in the time of the King of Kings Yoḥannǝs...’, a short historiographical composition.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ተሪክ፡ ዘተጽሕፈ፡ በመዋዕሊሆሙ፡ ለነጉሠ፡ ነገሥት፡ ዮሐንስ፡</q>
                           <note>The note, in a mediocre hand, was written during the time of King  <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName> (r. <date>1872–1889</date>), 
                              Nǝbura ʾƎd <persName ref="PRS5622Iyasu">ʾIyāsu</persName> and ʾAbbā Takla Hāymānot and ʾAlaqā Takla ʾƎsṭifānos from Gondar (the scribe?) ‘who was with them’. 
                              The note is a list of metropolitans of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church from ʾAbbā Salāma to ʾAbuna <persName ref="PRS2225Atnatewo">ʾAtnātewos</persName> (in tenure
                              <date>1867–1876</date>), with description of some events. It contains 107 names.
                           Besides, it mentions some rulers of Ethiopia and events that took place
                           when they were in power, such as King <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</persName> and the arrival of the
                           Catholic priests, the restoration of the Orthodox faith, the rule of King
                           ʾIyāsu, the conflict between daǧǧāzmāč Wube and rās ʿAli, the death
                           of <persName ref="PRS2225Atnatewo">ʾAtnātewos</persName> at ʿAdwā. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus from="181rb" to="181rc"/>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Extensive donation note written in the main hand. It states that the commissioner of the manuscript is ʾAbbā Gǝrmā Ṣǝyon who donated
                              it to the <placeName ref="INS0105DD">Dabra Dāmmo</placeName> monastery. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                            <note></note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <locus target="#1r"/>
                           <desc>The title <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስንክሳር</foreign> and the internal number of the monastic library (384).</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <locus target="#3r"/>
